.TH SUPERMGR 1 "March 2026" "SuperManager" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
supermgr \- unified SSH, VPN, and network device management GUI
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B supermgr
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B supermgr
is a GTK4/Adwaita desktop application for managing SSH connections,
VPN tunnels (WireGuard, FortiGate IPsec, OpenVPN, Azure VPN), and network device
provisioning with an integrated Claude AI assistant.
.PP
The GUI communicates with a privileged daemon
.RB ( supermgrd (8))
over D\-Bus on the system bus.  All privileged operations (creating tunnels,
managing secrets, device API calls) are performed by the daemon; the GUI
itself runs as a normal user.
.SH OPTIONS
.B supermgr
takes no command\-line options.  All configuration is managed through the
graphical Settings dialog.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/supermgr/settings.json
User preferences: theme, opacity, API key, master password hash,
auto\-lock timeout, and webhook notification settings.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
If set, settings are stored under
.IR $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/supermgr/ .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR supermgrd (8)
